  "text_preview": "\"hammer\" American Sign Language (ASL) ASL Lessons | Bookstore | Library | ASL University Main ► HAMMER: The American Sign Language (ASL) sign for \"hammer\" The sign for \"hammer\" is done by miming the use of a hammer. Grab an imaginary hammer using an \"S\"-handshape and make two quick strikes on an imaginary nail. (If you hit your thumb make sure to let loose with an imaginary yell. ;-) HAMMER: \"Hammer a nail\" Hold a \"pretend' nail in your left hand and hit it twice with your \"pretend\" hammer. Sample sentence: Do you have a hammer? Note: Yes, as a matter of fact, I can amuse myself for hours . Note: If you mean \"hammered\" as in \"drunk\" see: DRUNK Also see: DRILL PLIERS SCREWDRIVER TOOL WRENCH * Want to help support ASL University? It's easy : DONATE ( Thanks! ) * Another way to help is to buy"
}
